                            Preamble

  This Noncommercial Public License is a free, copyleft license for
software and other kinds of works, designed to ensure that the software
remains freely available to all for noncommercial purposes.

  The licenses for most software are designed either to take away your
freedom to share and change the works, or to permit unrestricted use
including commercial exploitation. This license takes a middle path: it
guarantees your freedom to share, study, and modify the software, while
ensuring that neither the original work nor derivative works may be used
for commercial purposes.

  When we speak of free software under this license, we are referring to
freedom of access and modification, not price. This license ensures that
you have the freedom to distribute copies of the software, that you
receive source code or can obtain it, that you can change the software or
use pieces of it in new programs, and that you know you can do these
things — provided such activities are conducted on a strictly
noncommercial basis.

